Name: chronic neutrophilic leukemia
Definition: A chronic leukemia characterized by neutrophilic leukocytosis with no detectable Philadelphia chromosome or BCR/ABL fusion gene.
Synonym: mixed mucinous and non-mucinous bronchioloalveolar adenocarcinoma

Name: chronic myelomonocytic leukemia
Definition: A chronic leukemia characterized by monocytosis
Synonym: mixed mucinous and non-mucinous bronchioloalveolar adenocarcinoma

Name: chronic eosinophilic leukemia
Definition: A chronic leukemia characterized by a clonal proliferation of eosinophilic precursors resulting in persistently increased numbers of eosinophils in the blood
